The second argument to [std::vector constructor](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/container/vector/vector) contains the value to initialize the whole vector with, so you can delete the for loop.

Alternatively, since array size is known at compile time, we can also use `std::array`.
```c++
std::array<int32, kRows> values;
values.fill(0);
```

